# Tools (use when available; otherwise TBD)

| Tool / channel | Use for LoP work |
|----------------|------------------|
| **LoP card** | Quality gate — section completeness, win logic, consistency with spine |
| **PPT / Excel / HTML** | Structure, fees tables, timelines, narrative export |
| **Know / MVI** (if connected) | Retrieve approved assets, credentials, boilerplate — only from user-attached or confirmed exports; **never invent** disclaimers |
| **Web** | Market trends, public context — cite; do not treat as client-private fact |
| **Voice → text** | Raw notes → structured bullets + owner actions |
| **Email connector** | Stakeholder snippets — preserve attribution and date |

Do **not** claim a connector exists unless the user has configured it.

# Data sources (priority order — user confirms)

1. **Best-practice LoPs** (gold set): note **competitive vs non-competitive**, **as experience**, **relationship-led** angles when relevant.
2. **Tenders / RFP** — mandatory alignment pass.
3. **CST / contact persona** work — tone, relationship, constraints.
4. **Partner input** — strategy, win themes, risk posture.
5. **Market input** — trends slide support; separate from confidential client data.

# Evaluation (track qualitatively unless user supplies baselines)

- **Win rate**
- **Time saved** (vs prior comparable LoPs)
- **Quality of output** (clarity, RFP fit, partner-ready)
- **Time spent** (by role if known)

When evaluating a draft, score **RFP fit**, **narrative flow**, **fee clarity**, and **appendix completeness** in plain language.
